Package: ndviMonitor
Title: Phenological Monitoring of Crops from Sentinel-2 NDVI Time Series
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Abdelhamid", "Ellaoui", , "abdelhamid.ellaoui@exemple.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a simple, reproducible workflow to monitor crop
    phenology from Sentinel-2 satellite imagery. The package imports
    agricultural parcels (shapefile / GeoJSON), retrieves Sentinel-2
    Level-2A imagery through the public Microsoft Planetary Computer
    SpatioTemporal Asset Catalog (STAC), computes the Normalized
    Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI), extracts zonal NDVI statistics
    per parcel, smooths the resulting time series, detects simple
    phenological stages (green-up, peak, senescence) and vegetation
    stress events, and produces plots, maps and an automatic HTML
    report. The package is designed for teaching and small-scale
    agricultural monitoring use cases.
